title: Heavy rain, strong wind cause power outages, road closures
text:
Steady rain and blustery wind caused power outages and road closures Saturday as a storm system moved across the Puget Sound region.
Several streets started to flood when wind brought down leaves that blocked drains. It's resulted in standing water and road closures. The southbound lanes of Schuster Parkway in Tacoma, for example, have been closed by a mudslide.
The storm has left thousands in the dark from Grays Harbor to King and Snohomish counties. Streetlights have gone out in some areas, and police ask that drivers remember to treat intersections like four-way stops.
On the sidelines of an Edmonds soccer game, parents saw proof that fall is finally here.
"It's back with vengeance," soccer parent Brian Nielson said. "It's OK, I'm ready for it."
Ready or not, Mother Nature seems to have finally shifted seasons, and the traditional wet fall has officially arrived in Western Washington.
